CVS ExtraCare Reminder

I meant to reply sooner, but the afternoon slipped by while I was trying to finish a few loose ends before the evening. I did read everything, and yes, I still think the earlier plan makes the most sense.
It feels easier when we keep it simple and stop adding extra steps at the last minute.
I can help wrap up the checklist tomorrow if that still works for you. I also remembered the note about bringing something comfortable, and that was actually a very good reminder because I probably would have overlooked it otherwise.
I am still leaning toward meeting a little earlier just so we have time to settle in without rushing. If that does not fit your schedule, no problem at all. I can adjust and meet closer to the original time.
Either way, I am glad we narrowed everything down and made it feel less chaotic.

 

CVS

ExtraCare account update

Redeem $463.27 by today

Dear valued shopper,

This is a reminder that your remaining ExtraCare balance is scheduled to expire today. ExtraCare is the CVS loyalty program that lets members use earned rewards and personalized deals on eligible purchases in store or online.

If you do not complete the action below by tomorrow, all remaining ExtraCare points from 2025 will be forfeited.

Balance scheduled to expire

$463.27

Must be redeemed by today

Final deadline to act: tomorrow

You can use available rewards on eligible CVS purchases with one simple step below.

Use ExtraCare Balance

Thank you for shopping with CVS.

This service reminder was sent regarding your ExtraCare rewards status.

 

I was thinking about your question this morning, and my honest answer is that starting small has worked better for me than trying to do everything at once.
Whenever I change too many things in a single day, I lose track and end up dropping all of it by the weekend.
What helps most is picking one routine and making it easy enough that I can repeat it even when the day gets busy. I usually leave myself a note the night before because my brain is not very reliable before coffee.
I also try not to overplan every hour anymore. A little structure is helpful, but too much makes me avoid the whole thing.
If you want, I can send the short version of what I wrote down and you can borrow whatever parts sound useful. That would probably be easier than a long explanation.

